canonical_structure.name: UBX-RXM-SPARTN
canonical_structure.description: SPARTN input status. This message shows info on a received SPARTN input message. It is output upon successful parsing of a SPARTN input message, irrespective of whether the SPARTN message is supported or not by the receiver. This message is deprecated. Use UBX-RXM-COR instead.

bits.name: msgUsed
bits.description: 2 = SPARTN message used successfully by the receiver, 1 = not used, 0 = do not know

valid_variations.reason: Earlier or more general documentation versions group the final 4 bytes (offset 4-7) into a single 'Reserved' field, whereas later/more specific versions (LAP 1.50, HPS 1.30) identify the last 2 bytes as 'msgType'.

adjudication.reasoning: The extractions show the progression of the UBX-RXM-SPARTN definition. While all agree the message is 8 bytes long, later documentation (Extraction 1 and 5) reveals that the previously 'reserved' space at the end of the payload actually contains 'msgType'. Extraction 1 (from LAP 1.50) is the most complete as it also notes the message's deprecation in favor of UBX-RXM-COR.
